quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  8,45,"O ye who believe! When ye meet a force, be firm, and call God in remembrance much (and often); that ye may prosper"
  8,46,"And obey God and His Apostle; and fall into no disputes, lest ye lose heart and your power depart; and be patient and persevering: For God is with those who patiently persevere"
  8,47,"And be not like those who started from their homes insolently and to be seen of men, and to hinder (men) from the path of God: For God compasseth round about all that they do"
  8,48,"Remember Satan made their (sinful) acts seem alluring to them, and said: \"No one among men can overcome you this day, while I am near to you\": But when the two forces came in sight of each other, he turned on his heels, and said: \"Lo! I am cle ar of you; lo! I see what ye see not; Lo! I fear God: for God is strict in punishment"